THREE men were killed in a crash on Hendrik Potgieter near
14th Avenue on Sunday afternoon. When paramedics arrived on the scene, they found a BMW
ripped into several pieces. According to ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak upon
assessment, they found that three men succumbed to their injuries on the scene. “There was nothing that paramedics could do for them, and
they were declared dead,” said Vermaak. Vermaak added that ER24 also attended to other crashes that
claimed the lives of two people. During the early hours on Sunday morning, one person was
killed and five others were injured after a car rolled over along the N14 in
Brandvlei. “A pedestrian was killed in a hit-and-run in Krugersdorp
while another pedestrian sustained serious injuries in a collision in
Vereeniging. Nine people were injured in two separate collisions.” Six were also injured in a three-vehicle collision along
Robert Broom in Krugersdorp, while three people were injured when a vehicle
crashed into the back of a truck along the N1 north at the Soweto Highway.